ve%20AI%2C%20which%20encourages%20people%20to%20recognise%20and%20involve%20themselves%20in%20art%20forms%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20artist%20from%20Puducherry%2C%20Rajkumar%20Sthabathy%20suggested%20that%20no%20AI%20can%20ever%20replace%20the%20efforts%20an%20artist%20puts%20in.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20work%20portraits%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20character%2C%20and%20that%20makes%20a%20lot%20of%20difference.%20I%20wonder%20if%20AI%20can%20do%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20smiled%20Rajkumar.%20He%20expressed%20confidence%20that%20no%20AI%20tool%20can%20replace%20an%20original%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%224678180483%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMumbai-based%20artist%20Vikrant%20Dattapreya%20Shitole%2C%20who%20specialises%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F110768%2Fartworks-by-shyam-kumar-self-taught-artist-watercolours-on-canvas%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewatercolour%20paintings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20concern%20when%20we%20see%20AI%20take%20up%20so%20much%20space%20in%20our%20life%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20never%20a%20threat%20to%20an%20artist.%20The%20main%20purpose%20of%20art%20is%20expression%20and%20satisfaction%2C%20which%20AI%20can%20not%20provide.%20Also%2C%20it%20is%20ethically%20not%20right%20to%20use%20art%20and%20anime%20by%20AI.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAI%20might%20be%20transforming%20art%20today%2C%20but%20have%20you%20ever%20wondered%20about%20the%20traditional%20Indian%20art%20forms%20that%20have%20stood%20the%20test%20of%20time%3F%20While%20social%20media%20is%20flooded%20with%20Ghibli-style%20AI%20creations%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20visual%20storytelling%20traditions%E2%80%94like%20Madhubani%2C%20Kalamkari%2C%20and%20Raja%20Ravi%20Varma%E2%80%99s%20painting%20style%E2%80%94have%20mesmerised%20audiences%20for%20generations.%20What%20makes%20them%20so%20unique%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBeyond%20the%20AI%20hype%3A%20Have%20you%20seen%20these%20timeless%20Indian%20art%20forms%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ghibli-style%20AI%20art%20has%20taken%20over%20social%20media%2C%20it%20has%20also%20reignited%20discussions%20about%20artistic%20originality%2C%20effort%2C%20and%20ethics.%20Many%20artists%20agree%20that%20AI%20can%20never%20replicate%20the%20soul%20of%20human-made%20art.%20But%20beyond%20this%20debate%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20another%20exciting%20conversation%20to%20be%20had%E2%80%94one%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20incredible%20artistic%20heritage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20chasing%20fleeting%20digital%20trends%2C%20why%20not%20celebrate%20and%20explore%20homegrown%20art%20forms%20that%20have%20stood%20the%20test%20of%20time%3F%20From%20the%20intricate%20strokes%20of%20Madhubani%20to%20the%20storytelling%20magic%20of%20Amar%20Chitra%20Katha%2C%20these%20styles%20offer%20a%20glimpse%20into%20India%E2%80%99s%20rich%20artistic%20traditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMadhubani%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F227810%2Fmadhubani-artist-baua-devi-padma-shri-jitwarpur-photo-story-legend-india-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMadhubani%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Mithila%20painting%2C%20is%20a%20traditional%20Indian%20folk%20art%20known%20for%20its%20intricate%20patterns%2C%20bold%20lines%2C%20and%20vibrant%20use%20of%20natural%20colors.%20It%20typically%20depicts%20mythology%2C%20nature%2C%20and%20cultural%20themes%20using%20geometric%20and%20symmetrical%20designs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIts%20origin%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20art%20form%20dates%20back%20to%20at%20least%20the%207th%20century%20and%20originates%20from%20the%20Mithila%20region%20of%20Bihar%20and%20Nepal.%20Traditionally%2C%20it%20was%20created%20by%20women%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20their%20homes%20during%20festivals%20and%20special%20occasions%20as%20a%20form%20of%20storytelling%20and%20religious%20expression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20it%E2%80%99s%20used%20today%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMadhubani%20has%20evolved%20beyond%20murals%20and%20is%20now%20seen%20in%20contemporary%20fashion%2C%20home%20d%C3%A9cor%2C%20stationery%2C%20and%20even%20digital%20art.%20It%20remains%20a%20celebrated%20art%20form%2C%20gaining%20international%20recognition%20and%20being%20adapted%20in%20modern%20design%20while%20preserving%20its%20cultural%20essence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAmar%20Chitra%20katha%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20one%20style%20that%20is%20quite%20popular%20and%20close%20to%20how%20Ghibli%20studio%20anime%20looks.%20The%20comic%20book%20publisher%20illustrates%20stories%20based%20on%20religious%20leaders%20and%20epics.%20This%20style%20of%20illustration%20has%20enthralled%20both%20adults%20and%20kids%20for%20generations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIts%20origin%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20series%20was%20first%20founded%20in%201967%20by%20Anant%20Pai.%20The%20word%20Chitra%20katha%20means%2C%20Chitra%20(picture)%20and%20katha%20(story).%20The%20motive%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20publication%20was%20to%20simplify%20complex%20texts%20into%20illustrations%20so%20that%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20consume%20for%20kids.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20its%20used%20today%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20series%2C%20even%20today%2C%20is%20considered%20as%20a%20cultural%20phenomenon%20even%20today%20among%20readers.%20It%20is%20available%20online%2C%20as%20books%20and%20on%20digital%20platforms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EKalamkari%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F259480%2Fandhra-pradesh-kalamkari-art-pitchuka-srinivas-new-york-germany%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKalamkari%20translates%20to%20%E2%80%98pen%20w%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F259480%2Fandhra-pradesh-kalamkari-art-pitchuka-srinivas-new-york-germany%2F%5C%22%3Eork%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20style%20of%20art%20is%20found%20in%20the%20textile%20industry%20and%20like%20Amar%20Chitra%20Katha%2C%20Kalamkari%20to%20depicts%20mythology%20and%20nature.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIts%20origin%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKalamkari%E2%80%99s%20roots%20date%20back%20to%20around%203000%20years%20ago%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20Telangana.%20This%20form%20of%20art%20was%20initially%20used%20by%20musicians%20and%20painters%20to%20narrate%20mythological%20stories%20on%20huge%20canvas.%20These%20canvases%20were%20found%20in%20temples%20usually.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20its%20used%20today%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20today%2C%20this%20art%20form%20is%20considered%20as%20a%20top%20pick%20among%20buyers.%20Thanks%20to%20its%20intricate%20designs%20and%20natural%20dyes%20that%20make%20it%20look%20bright%20and%20vibrant%20on%20fabrics.%20Today%2C%20there%20are%20two%20types%20of%20Kalamkaris%3A%20Srikalahasti%20and%20Machilipatnam.%20Srikalahasti%20style%20depicts%20free-hand%20paintings%2C%20while%20Machilipatnam%20is%20block-printng.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERaja%20Ravi%20verma%20painting%20style%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhibli%20might%20be%20cool%2C%20yes.%20But%20how%20about%20having%20an%20image%20generated%20in%20Raja%20Ravi%20Verma%E2%80%99s%20style.%20Classy%20would%20be%20the%20right%20word.%20Raja%20Ravi%20V