%20be%20made%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks%2C%20depending%20on%20Tehran's%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Tehran%20Times%20has%20learned%20that%20Iran's%20armed%20forces%20have%20readied%20missiles%20with%20the%20capability%20to%20strike%20US-related%20positions%2C%20amid%20ongoing%20threats%20of%20military%20action%20from%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20if%20Tehran%20does%20not%20agree%20to%20a%20new%20nuclear%20agreement%20on%20his%20terms%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20first%20term%20as%20President%2C%20Mr%20Trump%20withdrew%20the%20US%20from%20the%202015%20Joint%20Comprehensive%20Plan%20of%20Action%20(JCPOA)%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Iran%20nuclear%20deal.%20The%20agreement%20had%20imposed%20strict%20limitations%20on%20Iran's%20nuclear%20activities%20in%20exchange%20for%20sanctions%20relief.%20%C2%A0Mr%20Trump%20reiterated%20that%20his%20administration%20remains%20open%20to%20talks%20but%20stressed%20that%20Iran%20must%20demonstrate%20a%20commitment%20to%20limiting%20its%20nuclear%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran's%20newly%20elected%20President%20Masoud%20Pezeshkian%20responded%20to%20Mr%20Trump's%20comments%20in%20a%20statement%20broadcast%20on%20state%20media.%20While%20rejecting%20direct%20negotiations%20with%20Washington%2C%20he%20acknowledged%20that%20indirect%20talks%2C%20mediated%20through%20Oman%2C%20could%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%26quot%3BThe%20supreme%20leader%20has%20also%20emphasised%20that%20indirect%20negotiations%20can%20continue.%20We%20do%20not%20avoid%20negotiations.%20Rather%2C%20it%20is%20their%20unfaithfulness%20that%20has%20caused%20problems%20for%20us%20so%20far.%20They%20must%20prove%20that%20they%20can%20establish%20trust%20regarding%20decisions%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20this%20will%20materialise%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Pezeshkian%20said%20as%20quoted%20by%20news%20agency%20AFP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743395160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.c