22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fipl%2Ftop-stories%2Fwhy-is-ms-dhoni-batting-at-no-9-csk-coach-stephen-fleming-explains-after-loss-to-royals%2Farticleshow%2F119787197.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20Chinese%20Men%20Try%20To%20%26quot%3BRemove%26quot%3B%20Documents%20From%20Bangkok%20Collapse%20Site%2C%20Detained%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPolice%20in%20Thailand%20detained%20four%20Chinese%20nationals%20on%20Sunday%20for%20unlawfully%20entering%20the%20site%20of%20an%20under-construction%20building%20that%20collapsed%20after%20a%20powerful%20earthquake%20in%20Chatuchak%20District%20last%20week.%20The%20police%20said%20these%20men%20were%20trying%20to%20retrieve%20documents%20from%20the%20building%20site.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Chinese-backed%20construction%20firm%20is%20being%20investigated%20over%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%2030-story%20under-construction%20high-rise%20during%20Friday's%207.7-magnitude%20earthquake%20that%20struck%20central%20Myanmar.%20The%20unfinished%20building%20crumbled%20in%20seconds%2C%20sending%20a%20cloud%20of%20dust%20and%20debris%20into%20the%20air%20and%20trapping%20dozens%20under%20the%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20Major%20General%20Nopasin%20Poolswat%2C%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20of%20the%20Metropolitan%20Police%20Bureau%2C%20said%20that%20four%20Chinese%20nationals%20were%20apprehended%20for%20illegally%20removing%2032%20files%20of%20documents%20from%20the%20rear%20of%20the%20collapsed%20State%20Audit%20Office%20(SAO)%20building%2C%20without%20permission%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20the%20National%20Thailand.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EALSO%20READ%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmyanmar-earthquake-thailand-earthquake-a-china-connection-in-bangkoks-33-storey-building-brought-down-by-quake-8045516%5C%22%3EChina%20Connection%20Emerges%20In%20Bangkok%20Skyscraper%20That%20Collapsed%20During%20Quake%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20powerful%20quake%2C%20the%20Bangkok%20Governor%20declared%20the%20area%20of%20the%20building%20collapse%20a%20disaster%20zone%2C%20thereby%20designating%20it%20as%20a%20restricted%20area%20where%20no%20one%20was%20allowed%20to%20enter%20without%20authorization.%20However%2C%20the%20police%20said%20that%20on%20Saturday%2C%20they%20received%20information%20about%20some%20individuals%20removing%20documents%20from%20the%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20investigation%2C%20they%20located%20one%20of%20the%20Chinese%20men%20near%20the%20incident%20site%2C%20who%20claimed%20he%20was%20the%20project%20manager%20for%20a%20building%20construction%20project.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20probe%2C%20it%20was%20confirmed%20that%20the%20apprehended%20man%20had%20a%20valid%20work%20permit%20and%20that%20his%20company%20was%20employed%20by%20a%20joint%20venture%20with%20Italian-Thai%20Development%20Public%20Company%20Limited%2C%20the%20contractor%20for%20the%20building%20under%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20also%20located%20three%20other%20men%20and%20confiscated%2032%20documents%20they%20were%20carrying%2C%20which%20included%20various%20types%20of%20paperwork%2C%20the%20National%20Thailand%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20four%20Chinese%20individuals%20told%20police%20that%20they%20were%20subcontractors%20working%20for%20a%20contractor%20under%20Italian-Thai%20Development%20Public%20Company%20Limited.%20They%20said%20they%20entered%20the%20area%20to%20retrieve%20the%20documents%20that%20were%20needed%20for%20an%20insurance%20claim%20and%20were%20stored%20in%20a%20container%20that%20was%20being%20used%20as%20a%20temporary%20office%20by%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20the%20questioning%2C%20the%20police%20temporarily%20released%20the%20suspects.%20But%2C%20l