hip.%20The%20Russian%20president%20suggested%20that%20Ukraine%20should%20consider%20alternative%20leadership%20as%20part%20of%20a%20potential%20peace%20settlement%20-%20an%20idea%20Mr%20Trump%20dismissed%20as%20counterproductive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Russia%20and%20I%20are%20unable%20to%20make%20a%20deal%20on%20stopping%20the%20bloodshed%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20if%20I%20think%20it%20was%20Russia's%20fault...%20I%20am%20going%20to%20put%20secondary%20tariffs%20on%20all%20oil%20coming%20out%20of%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Welker%20quoted%20Mr%20Trump%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Trump%2C%20who%20has%20previously%20referred%20to%20Mr%20Zelensky%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdictator%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20had%20a%20tumultuous%20relationship%20with%20the%20Ukrainian%20president.%20The%20two%20leaders%20clashed%20during%20Mr%20Zelensky's%20recent%20visit%20to%20Washington%2C%20where%20Mr%20Trump%20criticised%20Ukraine's%20wartime%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Trump%20reportedly%20claimed%20that%20Mr%20Putin%20was%20aware%20of%20his%20anger%20but%20insisted%20that%20he%20still%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20relationship%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20Russian%20President.%20Mr%20Trump%20added%20that%20his%20anger%20would%20subside%20if%20Mr%20Putin%20made%20the%20%26quot%3Bright%20decisions%26quot%3B%20regarding%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20diplomatic%20efforts%2C%20Mr%20Trump's%20administration%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20broker%20a%20lasting%20ceasefire%20in%20Ukraine.%20Russia%20recently%20rejected%20a%20US-backed%20proposal%20for%20a%2030-day%20ceasefire%2C%20while%20intensifying%20its%20military%20operations%20near%20Ukraine's%20northeastern%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Trump's%20proposed%20secondary%20tariffs%20would%20target%20any%20country%20purchasing%20Russian%20oil%2C%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20Moscow%20to%20sustain%20its%20war%20effort.%20Those%20who%20could%20be%20affected%20are%20China%20and%20India%2C%20bo