%20without%20adult%20intervention%20(most%20of%20the%20time)%20is%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20social%20skills%20they%20are%20developing%20through%20these%20outdoor%20adventures.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cbeaa4c3-c3b1-43d9-bf25-64c98eefa7f6%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20get%20limited%20and%20monitored%20screen%20time%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20spring%202024%2C%20my%20husband%2C%20my%20two%20next-door%20neighbors%2C%20and%20I%20began%20having%20organic%20conversations%20about%20parenting%20and%20technology%20on%20our%20front%20lawns.%20Already%20noticing%20screen%20time's%20negative%20effects%20on%20our%20children%2C%20we%20all%20decided%20to%20read%20Jonathan%20Haidt's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Anxious%20Generation%3A%20How%20the%20Great%20Rewiring%20of%20Childhood%20Is%20Causing%20an%20Epidemic%20of%20Mental%20Illness.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%2C%20which%20explores%20how%20technology%20has%20contributed%20to%20a%20mental%20health%20crisis%20among%20children%20raised%20on%20digital%20devices%2C%20has%20many%20great%20takeaways.%20One%20of%20the%20book's%20core%20messages%20that%20truly%20resonated%20with%20all%20of%20us%20is%20that%20the%20decline%20of%20free%20play%20and%20the%20increase%20in%20screen%20time%20have%20severely%20harmed%20children's%20social%20and%20emotional%20development.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20millennials%2C%20we%20remember%20being%20children%20who%20could%20play%20outside%20with%20neighbors%20with%20little%20to%20no%20adult%20supervision%2C%20making%20up%20games%2C%20playing%20tag%2C%20and%20generally%20working%20on%20our%20social%20skills%20with%20our%20peers.%20The%20book%20suggests%20that%20kids%20need%20more%20unsupervised%20play%20to%20develop%20independence%2C%20problem-solving%20skills%2C%20and%20social%20competence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c5bf0d1-a2bc-49c3-b86b-9b57b2032a5b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20want%20our%20kids%20to%20have%20the%20childhood%20we%20had%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20all%20agreed%20that%20we%20want%20our%20children%20to%20grow%20up%20experiencing%20life%20outside%2C%20playing%20with%20neighbors%20the%20way%20we%20did%20%E2%80%94%20running%2C%20exploring%2C%20making%20mistakes%2C%20and%20learning%20to%20navigate%20conflicts%20together.%20It's%20about%20giving%20them%20the%20space%20to%20figure%20things%20out%20with%20one%20another%20rather%20than%20being%20absorbed%20by%20screens.%20Don't%20get%20me%20wrong%2C%20our%20children%20still%20get%20screen%20time%2C%20but%20it's%20limited%20and%20monitored.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20neighbors%20often%20stroll%20by%2C%20smiling%20as%20they%20reminisce%20about%20a%20time%20when%20front-yard%20play%20was%20the%20norm.%20Every%20now%20and%20then%2C%20other%20neighborhood%20kids%20join%20in%2C%20turning%20our%20little%20patch%20of%20grass%20into%20a%20lively%2C%20impromptu%20playdate%20filled%20with%20laughter%2C%20negotiation%2C%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20childhood%20moments%20we%20all%20cherish.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20world%20where%20children%20are%20often%20glued%20to%20tablets%20and%20video%20games%2C%20and%20the%20art%20of%20face-to-face%20interaction%20is%20fading%2C%20I%20feel%20incredibly%20fortunate%20that%20our%20little%20group%20of%20front-yard%20friends%20is%20embracing%20the%20kind%20of%20carefree%2C%20outdoor%20play%20that%20defined%20so%20many%20of%20our%20'90s%20childhoods.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWatching%20them%20play%20outside%20almost%20every%20day%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20the%20best%20childhood%20moments%20are%20often%20the%20simplest%20ones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraising-kids-with-nineties-type-childhood-free-range-parenting-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743342781000%2C%